comments:
Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Bodmin Rural 
    and Bodmin Borough.

Created 1.4.1974 by renaming the parish of Bodmin Borough. See 
    also Table 2, note (f).
Renamed 1.4.1974 to become the parish of Bodmin.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parish of Bodmin. Abolished 1.4.1939 
    and divided between the parishes of Lanivet and Helland.

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of Lanlivery Urban 
    and Lanlivery Rural.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Lanlivery. See 
    also Table 2, note (c).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Lanlivery in Lostwithiel 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 25.3.1896 and added to the parish of Lostwithiel.

Created 1.4.1968 by renaming the parish of Padstow Urban. See 
    also Table 2, note (f).

Renamed 1.4.1968 to become the parish of Padstow. See also Table 
    2, note (d).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Blisland.

Created 1.4.1898 out of the parishes of Egloshayle and St. Breock. 
    See also Table 2, notes (a) and (f).
